ption": "Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 630799571, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2MzA3OTk1NzE=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/I-compilemem", "name": "I-compilemem", "color": "e10c02", "default": false, "description": "Problems and improvements with respect to memory usage during compilation."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 6, "created_at": "2018-04-24T16:06:41Z", "updated_at": "2018-05-23T05:53:19Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Since `rustc 1.25.0-nightly (bacb5c58d 2018-01-26)`, it takes more memory to finish compilation in release mode. On my dev machine, which has 16GB memory, building pingcap/tikv in release mode often fails with OOM.\r\n```\r\nOut of memory: Kill process 12260 (rustc) score 212 or sacrifice child\r\nKilled process 12260 (rustc) total-vm:4881248kB, anon-rss:3458380kB, file-rss:0kB, shmem-rss:0kB\r\n\r\nerror: Could not compile `tikv`.\r\nwarning: build failed, waiting for other jobs to finish...\r\n```\r\nThere will be four rustc processes in the final step, and each of them will acquire 2GB+ memory. Hence finally out of memory.\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/50199/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/50199/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}